OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1775408752
OL,3,CWoman who's survived three strokes and
OL,4,Chad 13 heart ops says she feels
OL,5,C'blessed'
OL,7,FEvery three minutes, someone in the UK
OL,8,Fdies from cardiovascular disease, with
OL,9,Fthe condition affecting more than
OL,10,Feight million people in the UK alone.
OL,12,FThe charity is also urging people for
OL,13,Fdonations so they can help fund more
OL,14,Fgroundbreaking research to keep the
OL,15,Fnation's hearts beating.
OL,17,FMichelle lives with a pacemaker - a
OL,18,Fsmall device that helps to manage
OL,19,Fproblems with a person's heart rhythm.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
